@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@alexToken = course-alex-local-token
@rileyToken = course-riley-local-token

### Reset source data and vectors, then restore the nine pre-existing source articles.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/demo/reset

###
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/demo/seed

### Riley can read Tenant Red support evidence but cannot administer migration jobs (403).
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/migrations/knowledge-articles
Authorization: Bearer {{rileyToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### Start a bounded initial backfill as the course migration administrator.
# @name startMigration
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/migrations/knowledge-articles
Authorization: Bearer {{alexToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "batchSize": 3,
  "rateLimit": 0,
  "reindexExisting": false
}

### Paste jobId from startMigration. COMPLETED means scanning/enqueueing finished.
@jobId = replace-with-job-id
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/migrations/knowledge-articles/{{jobId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{alexToken}}

### Wait separately for pendingQueueEntries=0, processingQueueEntries=0, and indexingCaughtUp=true.
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/migrations/knowledge-articles/{{jobId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{alexToken}}

### Prove the derived evidence is retrievable through the tenant-filtered application API.
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/knowledge/search?q=I%20cannot%20sign%20in%20after%20too%20many%20attempts
Authorization: Bearer {{alexToken}}

### Rerun with reindexExisting=false. Vector identity and completed queue count remain stable.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/migrations/knowledge-articles
Authorization: Bearer {{alexToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "batchSize": 4,
  "rateLimit": 0,
  "reindexExisting": false
}
